<h2 class="text-center">Shishqebap me Mish Pule (Chicken Kebabs)</h2>
<div class="smaller-space"></div>
<div class="container-fluid well well-lg">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <br />
                    <img class="img-responsive" src="~/Images/Albania/Starters/Chicken_Kebabs.webp" alt="Chicken Kebabs" />
                    <br/><br />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="text-left"><h2>Ingredients</h2></div>
                    <br />
                    <div class="text-left"><h3>Kebabs</h3></div>
                    <br/>
                    <ul>
                        <li>400g Cubed Chicken Breast</li>
                        <li>1 Cubed Red Pepper</li>
                        <li>Sliced Salami (Preferably Albanian)</li>
                    </ul>
                    <div class="smaller-space"></div>
                    <div class="text-left"><h3>Marinade</h3></div>
                    <br/>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Salt</li>
                        <li>Pepper</li>
                        <li>2 Cloves Diced Garlic</li>
                        <li>1 Tbsp Paprika</li>
                        <li>1 Tbsp Honey</li>
                        <li>1 Tbsp Dried Oregano</li>
                        <li>2 Tbsp Olive Oil</li>
                    </ul>
                    <br/><br />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h2 class="text-center">Method</h2>
                    <br />
                    <ol class="text-justify">
                        <li>
                            (Note - If using Wooden Skewers be sure to soak them first)
                            <br /><br />
                            Skewer in this order - chicken, pepper, salami.
                            <br /><br />
                            Continue until you have used all of the ingredients (this should make approx. 5 kebabs)
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Mix all the marinade ingredients together, brush over chicken, cover in cling film and marinate for at least half an hour (overnight will impart more flavour).
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>Place the kebabs on a grilling machine such as a George Foreman, close the lid and cook for 10 -12 minutes on a high setting. Turn the kebabs occasionally. You can also cook these kebabs under the grill on a baking tray or on the BBQ. Once cooked, plate up and serve with a side salad, grilled vegetables, your favourite condiments or pitta bread (or all of them! :D).</li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

