<h2 class="text-center">Byrek me Mish Dhe Spinaq (Meat and Spinach Pie)</h2>
<div class="smaller-space"></div>
<div class="container-fluid well well-lg">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <br />
                    <img class="img-responsive" src="~/Images/Albania/Starters/Filo_Pie.webp" alt="Filo Pie" />
                    <br />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="text-left"><h2>Ingredients</h2></div>
                    <br />
                    <ul>
                        <li>1 Pack of Filo Pastry</li>
                        <li>750g Mince Beef</li>
                        <li>1 Diced Onion</li>
                        <li>1 Diced Spinach</li>
                        <li>2 Finely Diced Potatoes</li>
                        <li>3 Tbsp Tomato Puree</li>
                        <li>1/2 Pint Beef Stock</li>
                        <li>1 Tsp Paprika</li>
                        <li>Salt</li>
                        <li>Pepper</li>
                        <li>Olive Oil</li>
                        <li>220ml Water</li>
                    </ul>
                    <br />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h2 class="text-center">Method</h2>
                    <br />
                    <ol class="text-justify">
                        <li>
                            In a saucepan add the olive oil and fry the onions for 2 minutes before adding the mince and browning.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Add the tomato puree, salt, pepper, paprika, potatoes and beef stock. Bring to the boil, leave to simmer for 10 minutes, once the mixture has thickened and the water has boiled away, turn off the heat add the spinach and leave to cool for 10 minutes as this will allow the spinach to wilt in the residual heat.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Layer sheets of filo pastry on top of each other brushing a layer of olive oil after each one before the next one is place down. Once 6/8 sheet are laid add the filling on top. Repeat the layering until a further 6/8 sheets are on top of the filling - olive oil brushed on each one.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Bake in the oven at 180 degrees for 1 hour or until golden brown.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

