<h2 class="text-center">Qofte të Fërguara (Fried Meatballs)</h2>
<div class="smaller-space"></div>
<div class="container-fluid well well-lg">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <br />
                    <img class="img-responsive" src="~/Images/Albania/Starters/Meatballs.webp" alt="Meatballs" />
                    <br />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="text-left"><h2>Ingredients</h2></div>
                    <br />
                    <div class="text-left"><h3>For Meatballs</h3></div>
                    <br />
                    <ul>
                        <li>500g Lamb Mince</li>
                        <li>1 Grated Onion</li>
                        <li>30g Breadcrumbs</li>
                        <li>1 Egg Yolk</li>
                        <li>10g Parsley</li>
                        <li>1 Tsp Paprika</li>
                        <li>1/2 Tbsp Oregano</li>
                        <li>1/2 Tsp Salt</li>
                        <li>1/2 Tbsp Pepper</li>
                        <li>50g Flour (for dusting)</li>
                    </ul>
                    <br />
                    <div class="text-left"><h3>For Breading</h3></div>
                    <br />
                    <ul>
                        <li>1 Tbsp Flour</li>
                        <li>1 Egg & 1 Egg White Mixed</li>
                        <li>15ml Water</li>
                        <li>Salt</li>
                        <li>50ml Approx Vegetable Oil</li>
                    </ul>
                    <br />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h2 class="text-center">Method</h2>
                    <br />
                    <ol class="text-justify">
                        <li>
                            Combine the lamb mince, grated onion, breadcrumbs, egg yolk, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper and paprika.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            With oiled hands mix and knead together until the ingredients are well combined, then divide into 14 individual meatballs and dust with flour.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Combine egg/egg white mixture the 1 tbsp of flour and water and start heating the oil in a frying pan.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Once the oil is ready, dip a meatball into the egg mix ensuring it is completely covered and then place into the frying pan and cook for  2-3 minutes on each side. Complete this process until all the meatballs are cooked, plate them up and serve warm with bread, salad and yogurt (alternatively they can be served skewered on toothpicks and dipped into a garlic yoghurt dip).
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

